http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Mysuru-Zilla-Panchayat-mobile-application-to-benefit-farmers/article13978062.ece

Chief Minister Siddaramaiah has said that technological advancement has helped the government run the administration more effectively and reach out to beneficiaries quickly.Many schemes were being implemented well using technology, he said.Inaugurating the Mysuru Zilla Panchayat’s mobile application here on Saturday, Mr. Siddaramaiah said advancements in technology should particularly benefit farmers and people from rural places. He commended zilla panchayat president Pushpavathi Amarnath for introducing the mobile app.The Chief Minister said that notification for the zilla and taluk panchayat elections would be announced on January 11 and the polls would be held in February. He asked panchayat members to introspect if they had done full justice to their responsibility in the last five years.“Being elected representatives, it is our duty to serve people by putting in all efforts,” he said, adding that their work and service as elected members would be remembered by the people.Mr. Siddaramaiah expressed regret for not holding the Karnataka Development Review meeting in Mysuru district for the last two years and said that he would hold one soon after the new zilla panchayat members took charge.Ms. Amarnath, MLAs Vasu, Somashekar, and Tanvir Sait, and zilla panchayat vice-president Madappa were present.